# Third-party packages the CPython 3.12 oracle needs so that every
# tests/cpython fixture that imports a 3p library can satisfy the
# "fixture must exit 0 under CPython" contract (runner.rs INVALID check).
#
# Union of top-level non-stdlib imports across tests/cpython/**/3rd-libs/**.
# Unpinned here; the committed requirements.txt (uv pip compile) is the
# content-addressed lock that defines the oracle environment's identity.
#
# Regenerate the lock:   uv pip compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt --python-version 3.12
# Materialize the env:   python3 tests/harness/cpython/tools/ensure_oracle_env.py
#
# The ensure tool also copies CPython's stdlib `test` package into the venv's
# site-packages. uv's python-build-standalone interpreters are `install_only`
# builds that strip Lib/test, but thousands of ported fixtures do
# `from test.support import ...`; without it the oracle exits 1 and the
# harness reports INVALID fixture.
#
# The harness auto-detects .cache/oracle-env/bin/python3 (harness_common.rs
# python3_bin); MAMBA_ORACLE_PYTHON still overrides everything.

